---

### 1. Make the layout fill width and most of the height

Update `dialog_symptom_logger.xml`:

- Change the root `LinearLayout` height from `wrap_content` to `match_parent`
- Add a max height to the `ScrollView` area using weight (already there) but well rely on bottom sheet behavior for 3/4 height.

```xml
<!-- Root -->
<LinearLayout
 xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
 xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
 android:layout_width="match_parent"
 android:layout_height="match_parent"
 android:orientation="vertical"
 android:background="@android:color/white"
 android:padding="16dp">
```

This ensures the content can expand to full width; the **3/4 height** will be controlled by how we show it (next step).

---

### 2. Show it as a bottom sheet at ~3/4 height

Instead of using a plain `Dialog`, use a `BottomSheetDialog` and set its peek height to ~75% of the screen.

In `SwasthyaAIFragment.kt`, in `showSymptomLoggerDialog()`:

Replace:

```kotlin
val dialogView = layoutInflater.inflate(R.layout.dialog_symptom_logger, null)
val dialog = Dialog(requireContext())
dialog.setContentView(dialogView)
```

with:

```kotlin
import com.google.android.material.bottomsheet.BottomSheetDialog
import com.google.android.material.bottomsheet.BottomSheetBehavior

private fun showSymptomLoggerDialog() {
 val dialog = BottomSheetDialog(requireContext(), R.style.ThemeOverlay_MaterialComponents_BottomSheetDialog)
 val dialogView = layoutInflater.inflate(R.layout.dialog_symptom_logger, null)
 dialog.setContentView(dialogView)

 // Force 3/4 screen height
 dialog.setOnShowListener { d ->
 val bottomSheet = (d as BottomSheetDialog)
 .findViewById<View>(com.google.android.material.R.id.design_bottom_sheet)
 bottomSheet?.let { sheet ->
 sheet.layoutParams.height = (resources.displayMetrics.heightPixels * 0.75f).toInt()
 val behavior = BottomSheetBehavior.from(sheet)
 behavior.state = BottomSheetBehavior.STATE_EXPANDED
 behavior.peekHeight = sheet.layoutParams.height
 }
 }
 ...
 dialog.show()
}
```

(keep the rest of your chip wiring code inside this function as is.)

This makes the sheet:

- **Full width**
- **75% of screen height**
- Slide up from bottom like a modern logging UI.

---

### 3. Let content use full width inside

In `dialog_symptom_logger.xml`, ensure inner containers also use `match_parent`:

- `ScrollView` already uses `match_parent` width.
- The inner `LinearLayout` is `match_parent` width.
- For the chip rows, keep them horizontal but not constrained; you may want to set `android:weightSum` and `layout_weight` for evenly spaced chips, which you already partly do.

If any chip row still looks too narrow, wrap it in a `LinearLayout` with:

```xml
android:layout_width="match_parent"
android:gravity="center_horizontal"
```

to keep it centered.

---

