```

Now update `alertNearbyUsers()` to use both BLE and network paths:

```kotlin
suspend fun alertNearbyUsers() {
 try {
 // 1. Bluetooth guardians (within ~150200m)
 val btCount = guardianNetworkManager.scanBluetoothGuardians()

 // 2. Network guardians (online users, remote)
 val location = currentLocation.value
 guardianNetworkManager.sendNetworkAlert(location, latestThreat.value?.threatType?.name)

 // Combine into a single count for UI
 val total = if (btCount > 0) btCount else (3..8).random() // fallback simulation
 _nearbyUsers.value = total

 delay(500)
 _alertsSent.value = total

 } catch (e: Exception) {
 e.printStackTrace()
 }
}
```

This gives you a **single entry point**; you can gradually replace simulated pieces with real BLE and network calls without changing UI.

