2. Click **Releases**.
3. Click **Draft a new release**.
4. Set:
 - **Tag version**: e.g. `v1.0.1`
 - **Release title**: e.g. `Naari Suraksha update`
5. At the bottom under **Assets**, drag and drop your `app-release.apk`.
6. Click **Publish release**.

---

### 4. Get the shareable download link

After publishing:

1. Open the release page you just created.
2. Rightclick on `app-release.apk` under **Assets**.
3. Copy link address.

It will look like:

`https://github.com/<your-user>/<your-repo>/releases/download/v1.0.1/app-release.apk`

This is your **deployment link**. Share this URL directly; users tap it to download the APK.

---

